e levitical sacrifice to Christ’s sacrifice. The earthly, levitical cult was efficacious when it corresponded to or synchronized with the heavenly sacrifice of Christ. Still, the author of Hebrews develops the notion of the heavenly cult in unique ways, as Christ’s sacrifice both validates the earthly practice but also, due to his new covenant theology, calls for its end. Ribbens’ bold proposal joins a growing number of scholars that place Hebrews in the mystical apocalyptic tradition, highlights positive statements in Hebrews related to the efficacy of levitical sacrifices that are often overlooked, and relies on the heavenly cult to reconcile the positive and negative descriptions of the levitical cult.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aJudaismxHistoryyPost-exilic period, 586 B.C.-210 A.D. 0aSacrificexBiblical teaching. 0aSacrificexJudaism. 0aTabernaclexBiblical teaching. 4aHebrews. 4aheavenly sanctuary. 4asacramental type. 4asacrifice. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Studies / New Testament.2bisacsh  aHebrews.  aheavenly sanctuary.  asacramental type.  asacrifice.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1z978311076250108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2016z9783110485394oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831104758900 cprintz978311047581440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311047713940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110477139423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110477139/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-076250-